{"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "schema", "document", "Document"], "kwargs": {"metadata": {"source": "https://minecraft.fandom.com/fr/wiki/Structures", "section": "Structures retir\u00e9s", "file_origin": "files/Structures.txt"}, "page_content": "- Structure : Nether Reactor Mod\u00e8le:Only | Biome(s) : Anywhere, as it's built by the player. | Description : A player-built structure that would turn into the Nether Spire , and would give the player access to unobtainable items. It was made of gold blocks , Cobblestone and a Nether Reactor Core inside. The reason for its addition is that The Nether didn't exist in Pocket Edition back then. This structure was later removed after the addition of The Nether, and the Nether Reactor Core remained unfunctional.\n- Structure : Nether Spire Nether Spire Mod\u00e8le:Only | Biome(s) : Anywhere where the Nether Reactor was built. | Description : A tall and round structure that spawned over the Nether Reactor. It was made out of netherrack, which was later changed to obsidian. It would also spawn various Zombie Pigmen and items like glowstone dust , Quartz from The Nether , and sugarcane , cacti , and seeds . Its purpose was to enable players on Pocket Edition to obtain certain items, as The Nether had not been implemented yet. This structure was later removed after the addition of The Nether; however, items such as seeds, cacti, and sugarcane could still be obtained in the Overworld.\n- Structure : Obsidian Wall | Biome(s) : Anywhere, since it stretched towards every direction. | Description : A 2 block tall obsidian wall which was only present during some versions of the Infdev phase. It started in the middle of the world, and stretched towards North, South, West and East. This structure doesn't have an official name.", "type": "Document"}}